node.text:
RECREATING ASIAN MOVIE CHARACTERS! 🎥
.
Thank you to everyone who volunteered your favourite movie characters played by Asians! It was really interesting to explore films I don’t watch and to find out how Asians are represented in movies from different eras, languages, genres, and platforms.
.
This challenge was borne out of a desire to dress up as my favourite movie characters but I soon felt a bit hollow dressing up as characters who didn’t reflect what I looked like. I’m so happy to learn that Asian representation is growing in mainstream media in various genres!
.
A moment of silence for the characters I wanted to dress up as but didn’t have the clothes to do so 😢
.
Swipe to see side by sides of the characters I recreated:
1. Anna May Wong, the first Chinese American Hollywood movie star. Played by @michellekrusiec in @hollywoodnetflix
2. Sasha Tran, played by @aliwong in Always Be My Maybe
3. Rose Tico, played by @kellymarietran in @starwars: The Last Jedi
4 & 5. Rachel Chu, played by @constancewu in @crazyrichasians
6. Alex Munday, played by @lucyliu in Charlie’s Angels (2000, 2003)
7. Amber, played by @jamiejchung in Sucker Punch
8. Astrid Leong, played by @gemma_chan in @crazyrichasians
@valerieharley HAHAHA i’m digging into the ones in storage already!
WHY DO YOU HAVE SO MUCH CLOTHES!!!! 😍
SIS SLAYED THIS ONE OKAY!!!! YESSSS
@everestsays thank you!! i’m just a hoarder 😂😂😂
👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻 Love this series!! U have a huge wardrobe!!!!
